   - `vmirror(piece)` can produce the horizontally mirrored version of the input grid.  
   - `equality(a, b)` compares two grids cell‑by‑cell, yielding a grid of booleans.  
   - If the original grid equals its vertical mirror, every cell of the equality result will be `True`.  
   - `branch(condition, a, b)` can select between two candidate outputs based on a boolean condition.  
